---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts.js';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="The terms and conditions governing your use of Pet-GoToPro — in plain language, without the legalese."
>
  <section class="category-hero">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="breadcrumbs">
        <a href="/">Home</a> › <span aria-current="page">Terms of Service</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="hero-lede">
        The rules for using Pet-GoToPro — written in plain language, kept as short as we can make them.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="page-content prose">
    <p style="background: var(--bg-warm); border-left: 3px solid var(--cta); padding: 1rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 0 var(--radius) var(--radius) 0;">
      <strong>The short version:</strong> Welcome, enjoy the site, don't steal our content, and please remember that nothing we write is a substitute for professional veterinary advice. If you use our affiliate links, thanks — that's how we keep the lights on.
    </p>

    <p style="color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem;">
      <em>Effective date: April 2026 · Last updated: April 2026</em>
    </p>

    <h2>Agreement to these terms</h2>
    <p>
      By accessing or using Pet-GoToPro.com (the "Site"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you don't agree, please don't use the Site. We may update these terms from time to time, and continued use of the Site after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated terms. We'll always date the current version at the top of this page so you can see when changes occurred.
    </p>

    <h2>About Pet-GoToPro</h2>
    <p>
      Pet-GoToPro is an independent pet product review and care guide publication. Our content is produced by human writers and reviewed by human editors, sometimes with input from veterinary professionals. We fund ourselves primarily through affiliate commissions, as explained in our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">Affiliate Disclosure</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Not veterinary advice</h2>
    <p>
      This is the most important section of these terms, so please read it carefully. <strong>Nothing on Pet-GoToPro constitutes veterinary advice, medical advice, or a substitute for professional consultation with a licensed veterinarian.</strong> Our articles are informational and educational in nature. They're based on research, testing, reputable sources, and in some cases input from veterinary professionals — but they are not personalized advice for your specific pet.
    </p>
    <p>
      Every pet is different. The dosing guidance that's safe for a healthy 50-pound Labrador might be dangerous for a 10-pound Chihuahua with kidney disease. The enclosure temperature that's ideal for an adult leopard gecko might be too warm for a juvenile. Generic advice, no matter how well-researched, cannot account for your specific pet's breed, age, weight, health history, medications, or individual circumstances. <strong>If you're making a decision that could affect your pet's health, please consult a veterinarian who can actually examine your pet.</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      You agree that you will not rely solely on Pet-GoToPro for pet health decisions, and that we are not liable for any outcomes resulting from decisions you make based on information you read on the Site. This is not a technicality — it's a genuine plea to treat our content as a starting point for your research, not the final word.
    </p>

    <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>
      All content on Pet-GoToPro — including articles, images we've created, photographs we've taken, videos, graphics, logos, and the underlying design and code of the site — is owned by us or licensed to us, and is protected by U.S. and international copyright and trademark laws. You may view and read our content, link to our articles from your own website or social media, quote short excerpts with proper attribution, and share links to our content in personal communications. You may not copy our articles in full to republish elsewhere, scrape our content for training AI models without permission, remove our copyright notices or author bylines, use our trademarks or logos in a way that suggests endorsement, or sell access to our content.
    </p>
    <p>
      Some images on the Site, particularly product photographs, are used under license from manufacturers or retailers. Those images remain the property of their respective owners and are used on our Site for editorial purposes consistent with the relevant licensing terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Your conduct on the Site</h2>
    <p>
      We expect all visitors to use the Site respectfully and lawfully. You agree not to attempt to breach the security of the Site or access areas or information you're not authorized to access, submit false or misleading information through our contact form, send spam or unsolicited communications through any mechanism on the Site, impersonate anyone else, use automated tools to scrape, crawl, or harvest information from the Site except for standard search engine indexing, or use the Site for any illegal purpose. Violations may result in our blocking your access to the Site and, in serious cases, notifying law enforcement.
    </p>

    <h2>Affiliate and third-party links</h2>
    <p>
      Many of the product links on Pet-GoToPro are affiliate links, which are fully disclosed in our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">Affiliate Disclosure</a>. We may also link to external websites for reference, further reading, or context. We don't control those external sites, their content, their privacy practices, or their reliability. Your use of any third-party site is governed by that site's own terms and policies, and we're not responsible for anything that happens to you on a third-party site.
    </p>

    <h2>Accuracy and updates</h2>
    <p>
      We work hard to ensure the information on Pet-GoToPro is accurate at the time of publication, but no content is perfect, and facts change over time. Product prices change, formulations get updated, new research emerges, and companies come and go. While we update articles regularly and note the "Last updated" date where applicable, you should always verify time-sensitive information (like current prices or product availability) directly with the retailer before making a purchase. If you find an error in one of our articles, please email us at <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a> and we'll investigate promptly.
    </p>

    <h2>Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
    <p>
      The Site and its content are provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind, either express or implied. To the maximum extent permitted by law, we disclaim all warranties including the implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement. We don't warrant that the Site will be uninterrupted or error-free, that defects will be corrected, or that the content is free of viruses or harmful components.
    </p>

    <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, Pet-GoToPro, its owners, contributors, and affiliates are not liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of the Site or your reliance on any content published on the Site. This includes but is not limited to damages for loss of profits, goodwill, data, or other intangible losses, even if we've been advised of the possibility of such damages. Our total aggregate liability for any claim arising out of or relating to these Terms or your use of the Site shall not exceed one hundred U.S. dollars ($100).
    </p>

    <h2>Indemnification</h2>
    <p>
      You agree to indemnify and hold harmless Pet-GoToPro, its owners, contributors, and affiliates from any claims, damages, losses, liabilities, and expenses (including reasonable attorney's fees) arising from your violation of these Terms, your misuse of the Site, or your infringement of any third party's rights.
    </p>

    <h2>Governing law and dispute resolution</h2>
    <p>
      These Terms are governed by the laws of the United States and the state in which Pet-GoToPro is legally domiciled, without regard to conflict of law principles. Any dispute arising out of or relating to these Terms or your use of the Site shall be resolved through binding arbitration in accordance with the Commercial Arbitration Rules of the American Arbitration Association, with the arbitration conducted in English. You waive any right to participate in class actions. This arbitration clause does not apply to claims that qualify for small claims court.
    </p>

    <!--
      NOTE TO SITE OWNER:
      Once you formalize the business entity for Pet-GoToPro (LLC,
      sole proprietorship, etc.), update the governing law clause
      above with the specific state your business is registered in.
      A Delaware or Wyoming LLC is common for online businesses.
      Consult a lawyer for your specific situation.
    -->

    <h2>Severability</h2>
    <p>
      If any provision of these Terms is found to be unenforceable, the remaining provisions will continue in full force and effect. The unenforceable provision will be replaced with an enforceable provision that most closely matches the intent of the original.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these Terms of Service should be directed to <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.
    </p>

    <p style="color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border);">
      <em>These Terms of Service were last updated in April 2026.</em>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
